default&#xa0;defaultRecommendations default15.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGiven the growing problem of crime in the wholesale sector, the FWD continues to call for the following immediate policy responses:
default&#xa0;
default16.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPolice forces should mobilise more resources and draw up appropriate strategies to tackle business crimedefault.default In this vein, the FWD believes that the advent of 
defaulte
defaultlected Police Commissioners presents an opportunity to ensure that
default area policing
default strategies to tackle business crime 
defaultinclude measures to address crime against wholesalers. These should be 
defaultproperly developed alongside meaningful local business engagement and consultation. 
defaultMore attention should also be paid to the role that serious organised crime plays in fuelling criminal activity against wholesale, particularly in cases of theft of tobacco products.
default&#xa0;
default17.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultA joined up approach among defaultneighbouring police forces, by sharing information and interacting more effectivelydefault. Often in cases of vehicle theft in which the criminal target is in transit crossing different police force boundaries there is confusion as to which force is ultimately responsible.
default 
defaultFurthermore, without effective cooperation it is difficult for different police forces to recognise patterns when crimes are committed in different policing authorities.
defaultAbout defaultFWDdefault Membersdefault18.
